<subSubSection lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1437,1224,2043]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1908,1934]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Remarks:</emphasis>
The pinned 
<typeStatus box="[457,555,1908,1934]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">holotype</typeStatus>
was in poor shape, with a rusted pin that had damaged the mesosoma, with the remaining parts (head, legs, wings and metasoma) loosely attached and disintegrating. To preserve the type, it was remounted on a card. The metasoma of the 
<typeStatus box="[630,728,1980,2006]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">holotype</typeStatus>
was dissected to extract the genitalia, which are mounted under the rectangular cover on S1. The head and metasoma of the 
<typeStatus box="[822,918,2017,2043]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">paratype</typeStatus>
are missing.
</paragraph>
